-- VDI 3682 Blatt 3 — Phase-2 rules: FPD_Characteristic constraints (E1/E2/E4/E5).
--
-- Linguistically these are PURE OCL, but they are NOT yet executable against the
-- CAEX serialization: the binding does not expose characteristics as enumerable
-- OCL instances (FPD_Characteristic is unknown to the type registry). Running them
-- today would yield a vacuous pass — the engine instead reports "context type
-- unknown to the model binding" as a diagnostic. They move into
-- vdi3682-pure-rules.ocl once the characteristic binding lands.

context FPD_Characteristic inv CharacteristicCategoryPresent:
  self.category->notEmpty()

context FPD_Characteristic inv CharacteristicDescriptivePresent:
  self.descriptiveElement->notEmpty()

context FPD_Characteristic::RelationalElement inv RelationalElementResolvable:
  self.references->forAll(ref | self.project.containedElement->exists(e | e.identification.uniqueIdent = ref))

context FPD_Characteristic::DescriptiveElement inv ValidityLimitsConsistent:
  self.validityLimits->notEmpty() implies self.validityLimits.lowerLimit <= self.validityLimits.upperLimit
